    <text id="A1413T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Having been accused of aiding Federal troops, Dr. Hilleary writes to Gov. Letcher
                    and asks for a speedy hearing so that he might clear his name.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient">To <abbr expan="Excellency">
                            <unclear>Exec<hi rend="super">ncy</hi></unclear>
                        </abbr>
                        <abbr expan="Governor">Gov<hi rend="super">n</hi></abbr>
                        <abbr expan="John">J</abbr> Letcher</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1861-08-07"><abbr expan="August">Au<hi rend="super">gt</hi></abbr> 7 <unclear><hi rend="super">th</hi></unclear> 1861</date>
                        <name type="place">Staunton</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I was <orig reg="arrested">arested</orig> and brought to this place by the order
                    of <abbr expan="Colonel">C<hi rend="super">ol</hi></abbr> Jackson a man
                        <unclear>unnow</unclear> to me on a charge of conducting the <orig
                        reg="Federal">Federall</orig> troops to the top of <unclear>Rich</unclear>
                    <orig reg="Mountain">mountain</orig> the charge is <orig reg="false">Fals</orig>
                    and <orig reg="I">i</orig> have called on <abbr expan="Colonel">Col</abbr>
                    Jackson to give me a Fair and <abbr expan="honorable">Honerabl</abbr> hearing on
                    trial and <add hand="h1" place="inline">would</add>
                    <orig reg="prove">proove</orig> to him and the <orig reg="whole">
                        <unclear>holle</unclear>
                    </orig>
                    <orig reg="Confederacy">ConFederacy</orig> that <orig reg="I">i</orig> am
                    innocent of Such a charge and <orig reg="I">i</orig> will prove also that no
                        <orig reg="man">mon</orig> that <orig reg="claims">clames</orig> to be a
                    Southern man that has done more than <orig reg="I">i</orig> have to promote the
                    cause of <add hand="h1" place="inline">th<unclear>e</unclear></add> South me and
                    my Family <orig reg="sir">Ser</orig>
                    <orig reg="I">i</orig> am <del rend="none" hand="h1"/> the Federal troops and can you or any
                    other man <unclear>then</unclear> For one moment that <orig reg="I">i</orig>
                    would leave my home and all <add hand="h1" place="inline">to</add> the <orig
                        reg="mercy">mercey</orig> of a <unclear>banded</unclear> Enemy and then
                        <unclear>aide</unclear> them in the destruction of the army and my <orig
                        reg="property">propety</orig> and all that <orig reg="I">i</orig> had why
                        <orig reg="sir">ser</orig> it is <orig reg="preposterous">proposterus</orig>
                    to think of therefore <orig reg="I">i</orig> wish you would order <abbr
                        expan="Colonel">Col</abbr> Jackson to give me a hearing and let me acquit
                        <orig reg="myself">my self</orig>
                    <orig reg="honorably">honerabl</orig> and let the Falsehood <orig reg="fall"
                        >Foll</orig> on the one that <pb n="2"/> the one that <orig
                        reg="perpetrated">perpotrated</orig> it <orig reg="I">i</orig> have been
                        <orig reg="here">hear</orig> For nearly three week From my <orig
                        reg="family">Famely</orig> and <orig reg="I">i</orig> am anxious to <add
                        hand="h1" place="inline">go</add> back to them at the Springs <orig reg="I"
                        >i</orig> never left the army <orig reg="until">untell</orig> the day of the
                    battle and the retreat and brought From <orig reg="therr">there</orig> in a
                    buggy <abbr expan="Captain">cap<hi rend="super">t</hi></abbr> W Ervin he was
                    very much crippled From a Fall in the camp and <orig reg="I">i</orig>
                    <orig reg="carried">carred</orig> him home near the warm Springs</p>

                <p>I am not in <orig reg="prison">prisson</orig> but brought <orig reg="here"
                    >hear</orig> and turned loose to run at camp but that do not S<del rend="none" hand="h1"/>
                    me <orig reg="I">i</orig> will not leave <orig reg="until">untell</orig>
                    <orig reg="I">i</orig> get Satisfaction <orig reg="I">i</orig> can prove my
                    Standing in life and now Sixty Five years of a<del rend="none" hand="h1"/> have <orig
                        reg="faded">Feded</orig> different Stations of office in life and there has
                    never been the least thing few of me before Your <orig reg="immediate">omedeate</orig>
                    <orig reg="attention">attenteon</orig> to this will <orig reg="greatly">grately</orig>
                    <orig reg="oblige">oblege</orig> a Friend</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute/>
                    <signed>D<hi rend="super">r</hi> Washington Hilleary</signed>
                    <seg type="postscript"><orig reg="Governor">Gov.</orig> John Letcher ,<lb/> I am
                        acquainted with D<hi rend="super">r</hi> Hilliary, and I feel satisfied that
                        he is a True Southern man, I saw him at Huttonsville, at the time of <abbr
                            expan="Colonel">Co<hi rend="super">l</hi>.</abbr> Scotts <orig
                            reg="retreat">retriat</orig> with a sick man in his <pb n="3"/>
                        carriage, I also saw him at <unclear>Greenbur</unclear> with the same
                        Gentleman, I <del hand="h1">am</del> feel Confident and recommend that he
                        should at once be released from arrest. -<lb/> Very <orig reg="Respectfully"
                            >Respectfuly</orig><lb/> D. D. Morrall</seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
